<% content_for :title, "SentryPact | Filtering that stays on" %>
<% content_for :description, "Lockdown-first filtering with timer-locked Solo Pacts, server-verified release, optional co-signers, tamper detection, and privacy-preserving accountability." %>

<section class="hero-section">
  <div class="hero-background" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="section-inner hero-grid">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Lockdown-first filtering and accountability</p>
      <h1>Filtering that stays on when willpower does not.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Make a timer-locked pact with yourself, block high-risk categories, detect bypass attempts, and keep accountability private by default.</p>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <%= link_to "Join early access", "mailto:hello@sentrypact.com", class: "button button-primary" %>
        <%= link_to "See the pact model", pacts_path, class: "button button-secondary" %>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-row" aria-label="SentryPact product metrics">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <p>72h</p>
          <span>Release window</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <p>0</p>
          <span>Raw URLs shared</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <p>18</p>
          <span>Attempts blocked</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="fine-print">Tamper-resistant and bypass-detecting. Not marketed as impossible to bypass, a medical treatment, or a guaranteed prevention tool.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="product-preview" aria-label="SentryPact dashboard preview">
      <div class="event-callout">
        <p>Tamper event</p>
        <strong>DNS changed</strong>
        <span>Logged, reverted, held until release.</span>
      </div>

      <div class="dashboard-shell">
        <div class="dashboard-topbar">
          <div>
            <p>Sentry Mode</p>
            <strong>Solo Pact active</strong>
          </div>
          <span>Protected</span>
        </div>

        <div class="dashboard-body">
          <section class="timer-panel" aria-label="Active pact countdown">
            <div class="panel-heading">
              <div>
                <p>Release available in</p>
                <strong>71:42</strong>
              </div>
              <span>Server verified</span>
            </div>
            <div class="progress-track">
              <div class="progress-fill" style="width: 61%"></div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <div class="dashboard-grid">
            <section class="panel" aria-label="Blocked categories">
              <p class="panel-kicker">Blocked categories</p>
              <div class="category-list">
                <% [ [ "Porn", 18, 76 ], [ "Gambling", 15, 65 ], [ "Proxy/VPN", 12, 54 ], [ "Malware", 9, 43 ] ].each do |category, count, percent| %>
                  <div class="category-row">
                    <div>
                      <span><%= category %></span>
                      <small><%= count %></small>
                    </div>
                    <div class="progress-track progress-track--small">
                      <div class="progress-fill" style="width: <%= percent %>%"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                <% end %>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="panel panel-muted" aria-label="Privacy summary">
              <p class="panel-kicker">Privacy summary</p>
              <div class="privacy-list">
                <div>
                  <span>Raw browsing history</span>
                  <strong>Off</strong>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span>Category counts</span>
                  <strong>On</strong>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <span>Partner visibility</span>
                  <strong>Visible</strong>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="signal-bar">
  <div class="section-inner signal-grid">
    <p><span></span>Voluntary lockdown</p>
    <p><span></span>Server-verified release</p>
    <p><span></span>Bypass-aware alerts</p>
    <p><span></span>Privacy by default</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">The product idea</p>
      <h2>A pact is a voluntary lock with a release time.</h2>
      <p>Users choose categories, choose a duration, review what becomes hard to change, and confirm with serious friction. The server records the release timestamp so device clock changes do not end the pact early.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      <article class="feature-card">
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Timer-locked self protection</h3>
        <p>24h, 72h, 7d, 30d, 90d, or custom durations with server-verified expiration and delayed emergency release.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="feature-card">
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Partner-controlled amendments</h3>
        <p>Optional approval requests, auto-expiring unblock requests, tamper alerts, and privacy-preserving weekly summaries.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="feature-card">
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Bypass-aware enforcement</h3>
        <p>Detect DNS changes, disabled VPN, proxy tools, browser changes, revoked permissions, clock tampering, and uninstall attempts.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="feature-card">
        <span>04</span>
        <h3>Private by default</h3>
        <p>Category counts and tamper events are enough for most accountability. Full URL history is opt-in, never the default.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="section-foot">
      <%= link_to "Read the full pact model", pacts_path, class: "section-link" %>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section page-section-alt">
  <div class="section-inner split-section">
    <div class="section-heading sticky-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Build order</p>
      <h2>Native enforcement, Rails control plane.</h2>
      <p>The website, backend, dashboard, subscriptions, pact state, and signed configuration publishing live in Rails. Device enforcement stays native where the operating system requires real control.</p>
      <p>
        <%= link_to "See the product overview", overview_path, class: "section-link" %>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-list">
      <% [
        [ "v0.1", "iOS Solo", "Swift, local VPN/DNS filtering, Family Controls where approved, server-verified Solo Pact release." ],
        [ "v0.2", "Android Solo", "Kotlin, VpnService filtering, Device Admin friction where policy allows, same pact semantics." ],
        [ "v0.3", "Co-Signed Pact", "Partner web dashboard, approval requests, tamper alerts, weekly summaries, partner PIN/override." ],
        [ "v0.4", "Desktop and browser", "macOS, Windows, Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari, DoH detection, SafeSearch enforcement." ],
        [ "v0.5", "Family and groups", "Child profiles, schedules, device groups, co-parent roles, coach and recovery group plans." ]
      ].each do |version, title, body| %>
        <article class="timeline-item">
          <span><%= version %></span>
          <div>
            <h3><%= title %></h3>
            <p><%= body %></p>
          </div>
        </article>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing draft</p>
      <h2>A paid plan centered on Solo Pact.</h2>
      <p>The early business model keeps the acquisition tier useful while making timer-locked protection the first serious paid wedge. Final pricing will be confirmed before launch.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <% [
        [ "Free",      "$0",     "Basic filtering",  "1 device, basic ad/tracker and porn DNS filtering, manual mode only." ],
        [ "Solo Pact", "$6/mo",  "Main early plan",  "Core categories, lock timer, delayed emergency unlock, up to 3 devices, tamper detection." ],
        [ "Pact Plus", "$12/mo", "Co-signer layer",  "Solo plus partner approvals, tamper alerts, partner reports, and priority false-positive review." ],
        [ "Family",    "$18/mo", "Household coverage", "Up to 10 devices, parent dashboard, child profiles, schedules, and app blocking." ]
      ].each do |name, price, label, description| %>
        <article class="price-card <%= "price-card-featured" if name == "Solo Pact" %>">
          <% if name == "Solo Pact" %>
            <span class="recommendation">Recommended</span>
          <% end %>
          <p><%= label %></p>
          <h3><%= name %></h3>
          <strong><%= price %></strong>
          <span><%= description %></span>
          <%= link_to "Request #{name}",
                "mailto:hello@sentrypact.com?subject=#{ERB::Util.url_encode("SentryPact #{name}")}",
                class: "button #{name == "Solo Pact" ? "button-primary" : "button-secondary"}" %>
        </article>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <p class="section-foot">
      <%= link_to "Compare every plan", pricing_path, class: "section-link" %>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="trust-section">
  <div class="section-inner trust-grid">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Trust and safety</p>
      <h2>Lockdown cannot feel like malware.</h2>
      <p>Users must understand what they are locking before they lock it. Partner mode must be visible, consent-based, auditable, and designed against coercive control.</p>
      <p>
        <%= link_to "Privacy commitments", privacy_path, class: "section-link" %>
        <%= link_to "Safety design", safety_path, class: "section-link" %>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-card-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>Explicit consent</h3>
        <p>No stealth mode, no hidden installs, visible partner status, and clear release rules before activation.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Minimal reporting</h3>
        <p>Category counts and tamper events by default. No page contents or raw browsing history unless explicitly enabled.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Emergency release</h3>
        <p>Cooling-off windows, partner approval, and documented medical or legal overrides with an audit trail.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Honest claims</h3>
        <p>Tamper-resistant, bypass-detecting, privacy-preserving, and designed to add friction during high-risk moments.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="access-banner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Early access</p>
        <h2>Help shape protection that respects consent.</h2>
        <p class="access-banner__copy">SentryPact is pre-launch. Early testers will see the Solo MVP first, with no marketing list spam.</p>
      </div>
      <%= link_to "Request access", "mailto:hello@sentrypact.com", class: "button button-primary" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
